<paragraph id="D10D36F9990C2B3DBC86FD03FE39FB09" blockId="11.[159,762,541,1670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">
Morphology — Female: Integument striated; posteromedial margin of Cx-I straight; apodemes of Cx-II forming an acute angle; Cx-IV subtriangular in shape, with anterior and posterior margins converging to median line, posteromedial margin with a well protruding apodeme (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C990C2B3DBE7EFC52FD73FC5B" box="[573,698,940,964]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="12.[159,171,1574,1593]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,621,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-5@12.[242,1346,621,1542]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6: Hygrobates (Hygrobates) hamatus K. Viets, 1935, male, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – coxal and genital field; B – I-L-5 and -6; C – palp. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5395996" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5395996/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Acetabula in in a triangular arrangement, medial margin of genital plate indented in the centre. P-2 ventral margin weakly concave, distally forming a right angle, denticles covering distal 2/3 of P-3 ventral margins, P-4 ventral setae on the same level (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C990C2B3DBEEFFBA5FF0BFB09" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="12.[159,171,1574,1593]" captionTargetBox="[242,1341,621,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-5@12.[242,1346,621,1542]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6: Hygrobates (Hygrobates) hamatus K. Viets, 1935, male, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – coxal and genital field; B – I-L-5 and -6; C – palp. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5395996" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5395996/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
). Swimming hairs absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F9990C2B3DBC86FB51FEA4FA06" blockId="11.[159,762,541,1670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Measurements — Idiosoma L/W 844/638; genital field L/W 153/187, genital plate L 114 – 116. Palp: total L 427, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 23/35, 0.67; P-2, 118/73, 1.62; P-3, 95/69, 1.39; P-4, 155/28, 5.5; P-5, 36/12, 3.1; L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.76. Legs: dL of I-L: 63, 103, 133, 173, 178, 159; dL of IV-L: 166, 150, 221, 266, 311, 241.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F9990C2B3DBC86FA4CFE48F9AC" blockId="11.[159,762,541,1670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">
Remarks — The single female from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A57669990C2B3DBE28FA4CFD07FA55" box="[619,718,1458,1482]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
fits the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A990C2B3DBD97FA2BFECAF98F" authority="K. Viets, 1935" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB990C2B3DBD97FA2BFD79FA72" box="[468,688,1493,1517]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Hygrobates hamatus</emphasis>
K. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5234B08990C2B3DBE94FA2BFECAF98F" author="Viets K." pageId="11" pageNumber="403" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref16928" refString="Viets K. 1935 - Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition - Arch. Hydrobiol., Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5 (3): 484 - 594, 5 (4): 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6 (1): 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Sumatra and Java (
<bibRefCitation id="B5234B08990C2B3DBE68FA06FD6FF98F" author="Viets K." box="[555,678,1528,1552]" pageId="11" pageNumber="403" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref16928" refString="Viets K. 1935 - Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition - Arch. Hydrobiol., Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5 (3): 484 - 594, 5 (4): 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6 (1): 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets 1935</bibRefCitation>
), but it is noticeable larger.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F9990C2B3DBC86F9B5FE7CF919" blockId="11.[159,762,541,1670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">
Distribution — A widespread species, known from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A57669990C2B3DBC9DF990FED5F919" box="[222,284,1646,1670]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">India</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="A9A57669990C2B3DBD03F990FE79F919" box="[320,432,1646,1670]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="403">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
